From: Dvir Chakim <dvir.chakim@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 19 Apr 2026 17:45:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] axl-aipu-core: import DMA_BUF namespace for kernel >= 5.15

The MediaTek Genio BSP 5.15.47 kernel (commit d011e19cfc68) backported
the DMA_BUF symbol namespace, so the module must declare
MODULE_IMPORT_NS(DMA_BUF) for this kernel. Upstream only adds the
import for kernels >= 5.16.0, which causes module load to fail with:

    metis: module uses symbol (dma_buf_attach) from namespace DMA_BUF,
           but does not import it.
    metis: Unknown symbol dma_buf_attach (err -22)

Lower the threshold to 5.15.0 so the import is emitted for both the
MTK BSP and vanilla >= 5.16 kernels.

Signed-off-by: Dvir Chakim <dvir.chakim@gmail.com>
---
 axl-aipu-core.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/axl-aipu-core.c b/axl-aipu-core.c
index 4aceed3..6361dd2 100644
--- a/axl-aipu-core.c
+++ b/axl-aipu-core.c
@@ -1730,6 +1730,6 @@ MODULE_IMPORT_NS(DMA_BUF);
 #endif
 #elif LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(6, 13, 0)
 MODULE_IMPORT_NS("DMA_BUF");
-#elif LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(5, 16, 0)
+#elif LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(5, 15, 0)
 MODULE_IMPORT_NS(DMA_BUF);
 #endif
-- 
